$ Coin [Bitcoin]
@ coin

Definition of a coin: chain of digital signatures.
-
A bitcoin is a number that is associated with a → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/address[Bitcoin address].

{ Creation of coins

  The first → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/transactions[transaction] in a → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/block is special: it starts a new
  coin which is owned by the creator of the block.

}
{ Fungibility

  Bitcoins are not fungible.
  -
  This is because each Bitcoin has a history and is traceable.

  It might happen, for example, that someone (a coin collecter) values a bitcoin that originated in the → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/block#genesis-block[genesis block]
  higher than any other bitcoin.



}
{ No Bitcoin per se

  There is no such thing as a «bitcoin» per se. There are only unspent → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/transactions[transaction] outputs which are
  referred to as coins.

}

